Your Personal Information We collect personal information about you only when you specifically and knowingly provide it to us.
Your personal information will be used to personalize your experience within Helicon Soft Ltd.

We may make aggregate, non-personal, information about our site's users (e.g. overall statistics) available to third parties for advertising and other purposes, however, information that personally identifies you will be kept strictly confidential and will not be made available to third parties without your explicit permission.
On occasion, Helicon Soft Ltd. may ask you for personal information such as your name or address.
We do this when you register for contests, promotions, or services that require registration or subscription.
We collect this information so we can administer promotions, notify winners, and track/verify compliance with our policies.
It may also be needed for purposes of compliance with federal, provincial and local laws and/or for editorial and feedback solicitation purposes.
This site gives users the option to remove their information from our database and to not receive future communications from us.
We also give users the option to change or modify the information previously provided.
Your Email Privacy We hate spam as much as you, that is why here at Helicon Soft Ltd. we will never rent or sell your email address (EVER) and we won't send you email that you haven't asked for.
We only collect your email address in order to send you newsletters you specifically request.
At anytime, you can unsubscribe. Use of Cookies Cookies are pieces of information left in the settings of your web browser to identify your computer to a website when you enter.
Whenever a website welcomes you and tailors data to your specifications, it is reading a cookie and identifying information you may have registered during previous visits.
Helicon Soft Ltd. uses cookies to record your viewing preferences help us estimate and report the size of our viewing community and traffic.
While these activities depend on the use of a "cookie", visitors to Helicon Soft Ltd. always have the option of disabling cookies via their internet browser preferences.
Users should be aware that when you are on Helicon Soft Ltd., you could be directed to other sites that are beyond our control.
There are links to other sites that take you outside of our service.
For example, if you "click" on a banner advertisement, you are directed away from Helicon Soft Ltd.
The use of cookies is an industry standard, and many major Web sites use them to provide great features for their customers.
Policy Changes Helicon Soft Ltd. may introduce new products and services to its users and members.
We reserve the right to modify this policy at any time by notifying customers, via the Helicon Soft Ltd. website, of a new privacy policy.
You can send e-mail to us with any further questions.
Please Note: This policy only addresses our activities from our servers.

Other sites (including those that we link to and third party sites or services which we co-brand, such as content partners) may have their own policies, which we do not control, and thus are not addressed by this policy.
Security Helicon Soft Ltd. has implemented multiple levels of web site security to ensure a safe online environment.

We maintain this site and all associated data with technical, administrative and physical safeguards to protect against loss, unauthorized access, destruction, misuse, modification and improper disclosure.
However, no computer system or information can ever be fully protected against every possible hazard.
But Helicon Soft Ltd. is committed to providing reasonable and appropriate security controls to protect our web site and its information against foreseeable hazards.
We use industry-standard efforts to safeguard the confidentiality of your personal information, such as firewalls and secure socket layers where appropriate.
To date, Helicon Soft Ltd. has not received any reports of security or privacy problems.
We welcome your questions and feedback. Please feel free to contact us.

We also give users the option to change or modify the information previously provided.
Your Email Privacy
We hate spam as much as you, that is why here at Helicon Soft Ltd. we will never rent or sell your email address (EVER) and we won’t send you email that you haven’t asked for. We only collect your email address in order to send you newsletters you specifically request. At anytime, you can unsubscribe.
Use of Cookies
Cookies are pieces of information left in the settings of your web browser to identify your computer to a website when you enter. Whenever a website welcomes you and tailors data to your specifications, it is reading a cookie and identifying information you may have registered during previous visits. Helicon Soft Ltd. uses cookies to record your viewing preferences help us estimate and report the size of our viewing community and traffic. For example, if you "click" on a banner advertisement, you are directed away from Helicon Soft Ltd. The use of cookies is an industry standard, and many major Web sites use them to provide great features for their customers.
Policy Changes

Please Note: This policy only addresses our activities from our servers. Other sites (including those that we link to and third party sites or services which we co-brand, such as content partners) may have their own policies, which we do not control, and thus are not addressed by this policy.
Security
Helicon Soft Ltd. has implemented multiple levels of web site security to ensure a safe online environment. We maintain this site and all associated data with technical, administrative and physical safeguards to protect against loss, unauthorized access, destruction, misuse, modification and improper disclosure. However, no computer system or information can ever be fully protected against every possible hazard. But Helicon Soft Ltd. is committed to providing reasonable and appropriate security controls to protect our web site and its information against foreseeable hazards.
We use industry-standard efforts to safeguard the confidentiality of your personal information, such as firewalls and secure socket layers where appropriate. To date, Helicon Soft Ltd. has not received any reports of security or privacy problems.
We welcome your questions and feedback. Please feel free to contact us.
